dct_title_s: Map to illustrate Sir H. Bartle. E. Frere's notes on the Runn of Cutch &c.
dct_description_sm: Includes elevation profile: A section across the southern part of the Indus Plain near 25° N. Lat. [vertical scale ca. 1:104,700]. Elevation from approximately 66° E (Sonmiani Bay) to 83° E (Ganges Valley) is shown. Rann of Kutch, Thar Desert, and drainage basins are colored. Relief shown by hachures. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 40 (1870), pp. 181-207; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v. 40 1870
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society by John Murray, Albemarle St., 1871.
London, 6 & 7 Charing Cross. : Stanford's Geogl. Estabt., [1870].
